If only the uber guilds could kill him, and he spawned at a rate of once every two days, don't you think that the ubers would get all their clerics epiced and then stop camping him (the way some guilds are getting as far as VS is concerned on our server for wiz epic, and yes they also have plenty of vs legs...)...you may see 3-4 enter the server per week for a few weeks but then it would taper off after a month or two when the people who CAN kill him have done so and the people who want to kill him are able to try it and see if they have enough power to get this awesome item for their cleric friends...I am not saying make him so hard that ONLY the ubers can kill him, perhaps as hard as a HoT named sorta difficulty, so that you must have achieved more than getting a zerg quantity of people together to kill him yet not have 6 groups of decked out level 60's...<br>
<br>
My point is bottlenecks due to long spawn timers suck!  Think of a better way to use risk/reward for nice items like this in the future VI...bottlenecks caused by the difficulty of the encounter are fun and satisfying to complete!  Perfect example is the end of the druid epic, once you have that level of power thru friends/guild the last mob is not hard to have a shot at due to a short timer....sure the last mob for the cleric mob should be 'harder' since the cleric epic is 'better' but a similar spawn rate would make this quest more FUN!  (fun is why I play games)<br>
<br>
This only applies for nice NO DROP items really, some items need to be limited in how often they enter game for obvious reasons (ie farmage/economy).<br>
